  "text": "All five xDS v3 transport protocol components were found under source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/ in envoy v1.31.2:\n\n1. **GrpcSubscriptionImpl** (grpc_subscription_impl.{h,cc}): Adapter from typed Subscription to untyped GrpcMux, handling per-xDS API stats/logging. It delegates to whichever GrpcMux variant is injected.\n\n2. **GrpcMuxImpl** (grpc_mux_impl.{h,cc}, top-level): The SotW (State of the World) ADS implementation using DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse. Implements GrpcStreamCallbacks<DiscoveryResponse>.\n\n3. **NewGrpcMuxImpl** (new_grpc_mux_impl.{h,cc}): The Delta xDS implementation using DeltaDiscoveryRequest/DeltaDiscoveryResponse. Manages subscriptions via DeltaSubscriptionState and PausableAckQueue.\n\n4. **GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory / DeltaGrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory** (grpc_subscription_factory.{h,cc}): Factory classes registered as 'envoy.config_subscription.grpc' and 'envoy.config_subscription.delta_grpc' respectively. The create() methods select the appropriate mux (SotW vs Delta) and wrap it in GrpcSubscriptionImpl. AdsConfigSubscriptionFactory is also provided for ADS mode.\n\n5. **XdsMux::GrpcMuxImpl** (xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.{h,cc}): A unified C++ class template parameterized on <S, F, RQ, RS> that can be instantiated for both SotW (SotwSubscriptionState) and Delta (DeltaSubscriptionState) variants. The template is explicitly instantiated for both in the .cc file. Supporting subscription state implementations live in xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.{h,cc} and xds_mux/delta_subscription_state.{h,cc}.",
